        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2017-12-19 19:44:06.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> two qustions :\n > 1) oom needs 40 g ram????\n\nI tested with that configuration but I'm not completely sure if it's working properly, maybe that's the minimum memory required to have services up and running without any workload\n\n > 2) how can this be used as a local env for devalopment?\n\nOne alternative could be deploying OOM using the OpenStack provider[1] and the desired component locally. Another alternative is trying to use the all-in-one configuration and using the build functions to populate the local registry besides the change in OOM to use that local registry instead of external.\n\n[1] http://onap.readthedocs.io/en/latest/submodules/integration.git/bootstrap/vagrant-onap/doc/source/features/openstack.html",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
